### 12. Benchmark & Correlazioni (only when benchmark is configured)

Include this section only when a benchmark was set. Omit entirely if no benchmark.

#### 12a. Benchmark Specification

```markdown
## Benchmark Comparison

**Benchmark**: [ETF name] ([ticker], [ISIN])
**Mode**: Single ETF / Multi-ETF composite / Saved portfolio "[name]"
```

For multi-ETF benchmarks, add a composition table:

```markdown
| Asset | ISIN | Weight |
|-------|------|--------|
| SWDA | IE00B4L5Y983 | 60% |
| EIMI | IE00BKM4GZ66 | 40% |
```

#### 12b. Comparative Metrics Table

Side-by-side comparison of portfolio and benchmark. Data sourced from Riassunto, Rischio (Drawdown stats), and Benchmark & Correlazioni tabs.

```markdown
### Performance Comparison

| Metric | Portfolio | Benchmark |
|--------|-----------|-----------|
| CAGR | X.X% | X.X% |
| Volatility | X.X% | X.X% |
| Sharpe Ratio | X.XX | X.XX |
| Max Drawdown | -X.X% | -X.X% |
| Avg Drawdown | -X.X% | -X.X% |
| Max DD Duration | X.X years | X.X years |
| Ulcer Index | X.XX% | X.XX% |
| Correlation | X.XXX | — |
```

Note: Portfolio CAGR/Vol/Sharpe from Riassunto tab. Benchmark CAGR/Vol/Sharpe may not be directly available — include only if extractable. Drawdown stats from Rischio tab "Statistiche Drawdown" section. Correlation from scatter plot annotation.

#### 12c. Correlation Charts

Image-only sections (visual charts):

```markdown
### Rolling Correlation
![Rolling Correlation](images/[PORTFOLIO]-[DATE]-rolling-correlation.png)

### Return Scatter
![Scatter Regression](images/[PORTFOLIO]-[DATE]-scatter-regression.png)
```

#### 12d. Correlation Matrix

The asset correlation matrix (`#unified-matrix-figure` with `#matrix-type-radio` set to "Correlazione tra gli Asset") shows pairwise correlations between all portfolio assets as a heatmap. This step is mandatory when a benchmark is configured.

```markdown
### Correlation Matrix
![Correlation Matrix](images/[PORTFOLIO]-[DATE]-correlation-matrix.png)
```

#### 12e. Holdings Overlap

The holdings overlap matrix (`#unified-matrix-figure` with `#matrix-type-radio` set to "Matrice di Sovrapposizione Holdings") shows the percentage of shared underlying holdings between each pair of ETFs as a heatmap. Switch the radio button via `computer` click (not JS) to trigger the Dash callback, wait 3s for the chart to update, then export.

```markdown
### Holdings Overlap
![Holdings Overlap](images/[PORTFOLIO]-[DATE]-holdings-overlap-matrix.png)
```

**Benchmark image filename convention:**
- `[PORTFOLIO]-[DATE]-rolling-correlation.png` (1400×500)
- `[PORTFOLIO]-[DATE]-scatter-regression.png` (700×500)
- `[PORTFOLIO]-[DATE]-correlation-matrix.png` (1400×1000)
- `[PORTFOLIO]-[DATE]-holdings-overlap-matrix.png` (1400×1000)
- `[PORTFOLIO]-[DATE]-efficient-frontier.png` (1400×700)

#### 12f. Efficient Frontier (optional, when benchmark is configured)

The efficient frontier chart (`#efficient-frontier-plot`) shows simulated portfolios as a scatter plot of annualized volatility vs. return, with special markers for Max Sharpe, Min Volatility, Max Return, and the Current Portfolio.

Include this section when the efficient frontier is available (benchmark configured). If per-asset constraints were specified, include the constraints table before the chart.

```markdown
### Efficient Frontier

| Asset | Weight | Min | Max |
|-------|--------|-----|-----|
| VWCE | 60% | 40% | 80% |
| AGGH | 40% | 20% | 60% |

![Efficient Frontier](images/[PORTFOLIO]-[DATE]-efficient-frontier.png)
```

**Rules:**
- Constraint bounds table is included only when the user specified constraints (omit if unconstrained/default 0–100%)
- Frontier chart image exported at 1400×700 (taller than standard charts to show the scatter cloud clearly)
- Optionally extract and display optimal portfolio weights from `customdata` if available:

```markdown
**Optimal Portfolios:**

| Asset | Max Sharpe | Min Volatility |
|-------|-----------|----------------|
| VWCE | 45.2% | 38.1% |
| AGGH | 54.8% | 61.9% |
```

### 13. Footer

```markdown
---
*Report generated by backtesto-agent*
```

## Optional Sections

Include these if available from the backtest results:

- **Rolling Returns** chart (image-only, after Portfolio Value)
- **Return Distribution** chart (image-only, after Yearly Returns)
- **Monte Carlo Simulation** chart (image-only, after Risk Analysis)
- **Factor Exposure** chart (image-only, after Composition)
- **Expected Return** chart (image-only, after Factor Exposure)
